@jai1 
> I would suggest to modify UnAckedMessageTracker instead of creating a new class.

Here I want to show what would be like of the 2 solutions (WheelTimer and TimePartition), and it would be easy for your review, and comments.
Once the decision is made by the reviews and comments, I will change it, or create a new PR.

>Change ConsumerConfig => setAckTimeout(time, timeunit, numOfSlots); // assert (numOfSlots >= 2);

It is also OK to use numOfSlots. Here tickDurationInMs is more directly, and may more easy to support Delay messages in the future.

>add new messages to list.get(0)
On acktimeout redeliver list.get(list.size() - 1); and push messages down from i,e list.add(i + 1, list.get(i));

my original thought it like this: new messageid add will always be inserted to tail slot, and in timeout task, we change the cursor of new head and tail slot.

